<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="888" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="129.[788,1380,614,1042]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">
<taxonomicName authorityName="G. M. Allen" authorityYear="1914" box="[790,1016,732,765]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="altilis">Scotophilus altilis</taxonomicName>
was traditionally considered a junior synonym of S. 
<taxonomicName box="[1184,1318,776,805]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="leucogaster">leucogaster</taxonomicName>
, until additional samples and molecular and morphological analyses confirmed it as a distinct species. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="888" type="multiple">
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6398398" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6398398" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6398398/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" targetBox="[174,765,624,1038]" targetPageId="129">
<paragraph blockId="129.[788,1380,614,1042]" lastBlockId="129.[175,1380,1051,1597]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[789,976,934,963]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Distribution.</emphasis>
