<collectingCountry box="[1128,1223,977,1002]" name="Sudan" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Sudan</collectingCountry>
, W 
<collectingCountry name="Ethiopia" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Ethiopia</collectingCountry>
, SC 
<collectingCountry box="[919,1119,1017,1042]" name="South Sudan" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">South Sudan</collectingCountry>
, NE 
<collectingCountry box="[1207,1372,1017,1042]" name="Democratic Republic of the Congo" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">DR Congo</collectingCountry>
, and SW 
<collectingCountry box="[300,392,1051,1084]" name="Kenya" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Kenya</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="129" pageNumber="888" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="129.[175,1380,1051,1597]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[175,425,1088,1121]" pageId="129" pageNumber="888">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Forearm c¢. 
<quantity box="[593,689,1088,1121]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.6" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" unit="mm" value="46.0">46 mm</quantity>
. Dorsal pelageis sepia-brown to pale brown; venter is light brown. Wings and uropatagium are uniformly dark brown. Ears are comparatively short and widely separated, with inner margin strongly convex and outer margin almost straight. Tragus tapers to bluntly rounded tip, with concave anterior margin. Eyes are small. Skull is medium to large (greatest skull lengths 16-5-20- 
<quantity box="[1285,1366,1246,1279]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
) for 
<taxonomicName box="[227,368,1287,1320]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Scotophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="129" pageNumber="888" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Scotophilus</taxonomicName>
, and sagittal crest is present.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
